 Magnetic: @{"documentation" LINK "magnetic_docu"}, @{"games" LINK "magnetic_games"},  @{"datas formats" LINK "magnetic_formats"} 
  
@endnode

@node "gemagnetic_general" "GEMagnetic: generalities"

 With new hardware comes new incompatibilities.

 I have great fun with my new Apollo's V4SA flashed with EmuTOS.
 
 Unfortunatly, Dan's GEMagnetic 0.8 could not work properly with this
 setup and was not displaying the pictures correctly on True Color
 screenmodes on this and others.
 
 So I coded a respawn version, to play at, hum... The Pawn, one of
 the first games that came with my first Atari 520STF in the 80s. 
 
@endnode

@node "gemagnetic_legal" "GEMagnetic: legals"

 The GEM part PRG GFA-coded and LDG interface C-coded C is freeware.
 Sources are provided for general knowledge.
 Adaptations and upgrades without the agreement of the author are permited.
 Monetizing on this work is forbidden.

 Attention : use this program at your own risk. I deny any responsability.

  
 The Magnetic library is located in the core of the MAGNEMU.LDG.  
 Copyright by Niclas Karlsson
 Written by Niclas Karlsson, David Kinder,
            Stefan Meier and Paul David Doherty
            

 Previous GEMagnetic 0.8 by Dan Ackerman aka Baldrick
  
@endnode

@node "gemagnetic_install" "GEMagnetic: installation"

 @{0U}Atari part@{0}

  Requires & uses:
  
  ú large amount of RAM, the more, the merrier.

  ú FreeMiNT advised. Tested also on MagiC.
  
  ú since 16 colors screenmode, but better start at 256 colors.
    One can run it in duochrome, but pictures won't be displayed.
    
  ú large screenmode size: though no limitation with low-end setups,
    it's intended for large screens.
    
  ú GDOS or evolved is better for font display. Text is columned in the
    main window, a strong CPU will compute widths. If not, use monospaced
    fonts on lower-end setups. 
  
  ú @{0B}needs the EdDI cookie@{0} (with offscreen VDI primitives supported) 
    to build pictures. NVDI and its offscreen drivers are strongly
    advised. fVDI only may be not enough.
    
  ú @{0B}needs the LDGM cookie@{0} to load the MAGNEMU.LDG (aka the Magnetic 2.3
    library). If not found, please install LDG.PRG from AUTO folder or
    launched at start from FreeMiNT bash or from MagiC's START folder.
    You'll find an AUTO\LDG.PRG version in GEMagnetic package.

  Locations:
  
  GEMAGNETIC.PRG <- GEM port
  MAGNEMU.LDG    <- Magnetic library and interpreter, besides the PRG,
                    since it's specific, no need to move to C:GEMSYS\LDG\

  GEMAGNETIC.DAT\SYS\GEMAGNETIC.RSC <- mandatory ressource
  GEMAGNETIC.DAT\SYS\GEMAGNETIC.HYP <- this guide
  
  GEMAGNETIC.DAT\LIBRARY\ <- where games files should be located
  GEMAGNETIC.DAT\BACKUPS\ <- where backups should be saved
  GEMAGNETIC.DAT\SCRIPTS\ <- where scripts should be placed


 @{0U}Games part@{0}
  
  The original Magnetic Scrolls games are not provided in the archives.
  
  You'll need to retreive your beloved games from the webpage:
  
  https://msmemorial.if-legends.org/magnetic.php (bottom of the page).
  
  For now, main *.MAG and secondary *.GFX are used. 
  *.HNT are also handled, for windowed Magnetic games (Wonderland, and
  upgraded version of Corruption, Fish and Guild of Thieves 
  in Collection Vol.1).
     
  Put them in wanted subfolder and/or GEMAGNETIC.DAT\LIBRARY\.
  
  You can Drag&Drop the *.MAG file, use VA_START or ARGV to start the
  game (same as ^N key shortcut).
  You may declare *.MAG files in the desk configuration to be handled
  by GEMAGNET.PRG, thus loading all with a double-click on *.MAG file.
 
@endnode

@node "gemagnetic_use" "GEMagnetic: use"

 Select the wanted game from the menu or ^N keys.
 In the fileselector, choose the *.MAG file which is the game image
 handled by the Magnetic emulator/interpreter.
 
 Then read the game text, and write something to play.
 
 Restore and Backup are intended for game reloading and saving,
 using internal games i/o functions. File extension should be *.BAK.
 @{0B}Maybe issues here.@{0} Tested OK, but I would not rely everything
 on them. Use also resume/save scripts.
 
 When restoring a backup, the state is cleaned. Picture may be not 
 updated. Prompt "inventory" or "examine" or look around to know
 your current state.
 
 If you happen to experience an (epic) fail, the interpreter offers
 choice to quit|restart|reload: @{0B}better use GEMagnetic menu options.@{0}
 Quitting with the prompt method may be harsh and risky for the
 Atari operating system stability.
 
 Note for windowed Magnetic Scrolls games, which are:
  - Wonderland and
  - upgraded versions of Corruption, Fish! and Guild of Thieves packaged in
    Collection Vol.1
 -> when you return to an old place, the picture is not updated and stays with
    the lasted displayed one, unless you ask "look" in the prompt.
 
@endnode

@node "gemagnetic_scripts" "GEMagnetic: scripts"

 @{0U}Resume@{0}
 
  Loads a *.REC file, basically a text file containing all prompts ie
  each commands lines.
  
  This function (re)starts the game and apply each line according
  to the method selected in the menu.
  
  ú 'send all commands' all at once. You'll see the final result and have
    to scroll back in the log to read.
    
  ú 'prompt step by step'. The prompt is filled but not send, use Enter
    key to validate and continue. You may change the line, but if changed,
    the next one will be the one you discarded. To exit this mode, change
    the method to 'send all commands' punctually. 
 
 @{0U}Save@{0}

  The sent commands list will be exported to a text file with *.REC
  extension. That may be a human readable backup.
 
@endnode

@node "gemagnetic_prefs" "GEMagnetic: preferences"

  Alerts: disable some of them, some for low-end unsupported systems,
          may be annoying at start.
  
  Notifications: BGEM.NG is used (preferences saving, gxalloc routines). 
 
 @{0U}Paths@{0}

  Library: the fileselector opens on this path for games files.
  Backups: ___ ____________ _____ __ ____ ____ ___ backups games.
  Scripts: ___ ____________ _____ __ ____ ____ ___ scripts records.
 
  Logging may be useful if any issues.

 @{0U}Texts@{0}

  Select font, height and colors. 
  
 @{0U}Pictures@{0}

  Display is enabled if EdDI cookie is present
                 and since 16 colors screenmode.
                 
  Size can be doubled (zoom *2) for huge screens.
  
  Size can be also divided (area /2) for small screens.
  Can correct for static images, but one should prefer
  original size (zoom *1) for animations.
  
  Animations are supported for windowed Magnetic games only.
    You may choose 'once' or 'loop' if you want it repeated.
 
@endnode

@node "gemagnetic_versions" "GEMagnetic: history"
 
 @{0B}1.1B@{0}
  - add: picture preference: size can be /2 (for small screens).
  - add: under SingleTOS, use legacy menu location instead of displaying it
         in main the window.
  - fix: restore palette for preferences, infos, icon, hints, fileselector.
  - fix: for games with animation, less memory use by flushing images buffers
         when loading new image/animation (remember to write "look" if you
         want to update an old picture/location).
  - fix: using SHEL_FIND() to find GEMAGNET.PRG and its GEMAGNET.DAT folder.
  - fix: missing path when opening the guide with ST-GUIDE.ACC and VA_START.
 Thanks Eero Tamminen.
 
 @{0B}1.1@{0}
 - add: Animations (1).
 - add: Hints, displayed in windowed treeview (call from Help menu) (1).
 - fix: magnemu.ldg size and memory footprint reduced (no more printf).
 - fix: magnemu.ldg does not access disk *.MAG+GFX+HNT directly, increasing
        stability under MagiC (LDG client load all and provides the files
        using memory buffers). Games backup/restore are still using direct
        disk access though.
 - fix: magnemu.ldg calls ldg_Malloc() and ldg_Free() correctly.
 - fix: enables graphics and hints automaticaly (1).
 - fix: 'u:\pipe\dragdrop.' missing for Drag&Drop (visible under Magxdesk).
 - fix: wrong alert if GEMAGNET.HYP not found.
 - fix: discard CR from strings in *.REC files.
 - fix: vslider at top when starting game.
 - fix: hide status if not supported (1).
 - fix: last character of some paragraph got lost.
 (1) for windowed Magnetic Scrolls games: Collection Vol.1(which includes
     upgraded version of Corruption, Fish, Guild of Thieves) and Wonderland.
 Thanks Thorsten Otto and AL-FGC
 
 @{0B}1.0@{0}
 - respawn version. 

 @{0B}0.8@{0}
 - previous C-coded by Dan Ackerman aka Baldrick.
 
@endnode

